    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-07T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-07T13:00:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860A.01/7–744: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Navies</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Brandt</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-07T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 7, 1944—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>324. For Kirk. Murphy has reported that the Consul General of San Marino at Rome
                    has made representations through the British Legation to the Holy See regarding
                    the alleged recent bombing of San Marino. He inquired concerning the position of
                    San Marino and whether we should entertain representations of this nature
                    directly from the Consul General or through the Italian Foreign Office.</p>
                <p>The Department repeated to him its recent telegram to you<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d306fn1">See <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note> concerning the
                    relations of San Marino with the United States and United Kingdom. He was
                    further informed that prior to the outbreak of war the American Consul at
                    Florence has traditionally been the United States representative to the Republic
                    of San Marino. Since the Republic of San Marino has been generally recognized by
                    this Government as an independent state (see extradition treaty between U.S. and
                    San Marino, proclaimed June 12, 1908<note n="5" xml:id="d306fn2">Signed January
                        10, 1906; for text, see <ref target="frus1908#pg_710">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1908, p. 710</ref>.</note>)
                    the Department knows of no reason why we should not entertain representations
                    directly from the accredited representative of the Republic.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
